UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1134
1 Commonwealth of Kentucky, the Senate concurring therein:
2 Section 1. (1) The Legislative Research Commission shall establish the
3 Property Taxation Task Force. The task force shall study, review, and make
4 recommendations regarding the current and future policy needs of the state to address
5 rising property taxes affecting the citizens of the Commonwealth, including but not
6 limited to:
7 (a) An analysis of property costs, local property tax rates, and household income
8 statewide and regionally in Kentucky;
9 (b) A comprehensive review of state and local laws, regulations, policies, and
10 procedures that affect property tax; and
11 (c) Examine efforts and policy changes in other states and municipalities to
12 address property taxation.
13 (2) In the development of policy recommendations and strategies, the task force
14 shall seek input from organizations and associations whose members are impacted by
15 property taxation, advisory groups, researchers, and appropriate stakeholders as
16 determined by the task force.
17 Section 2. The task force shall be composed of the following 10 members, with
18 final membership of the task force being subject to the consideration and approval of the
19 Legislative Research Commission:
20 (1) Four members of the Senate to be appointed by the President of the Senate,
21 one of whom shall be designated as a co-chair of the task force by the President of the
22 Senate;
23 (2) One member of the Senate, to be appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of
24 the Senate;
25 (3) Four members of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the Speaker
26 of the House of Representatives, one of whom shall be designated as a co-chair of the
27 task force by the Speaker of the House of Representatives; and
Page 2 of 3
XXXX 1/9/2026 8:44 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1134
1 (4) One member of the House of Representatives to be appointed by the Minority
2 Floor Leader of the House of Representatives.
3 Section 3. The Property Taxation Task Force shall meet monthly during the
4 2026 Interim of the General Assembly. The task force shall submit findings and
5 recommendations to the Legislative Research Commission for referral to the appropriate
6 committee or subcommittee thereof by December 1, 2026.
7 Section 4. Provisions of this Resolution to the contrary notwithstanding, the
8 Legislative Research Commission shall have the authority to alternatively assign the
9 issues identified herein to an interim joint committee or subcommittee thereof, and to
10 designate a study completion date.
